<plot>In an observing way GRITO de PIEDRA (SCREAM of the STONE) gives an inside view of the lives of Gavino and Pedro Montes. Gavino is a miner in the Cerro Rico in Potosí,Bolivia. His son Pedro, a 23 year old student, works as a tourist guide in the same mine. The city of Potosí and its people didn't evolve much over the last few centuries. Over the last decade however, tourism has discovered Potosi; and the fascinating hardships of the silver mine. Already, tourism has left its marks on the town and its people.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?223229</url></doc>
